ollama_listen_all_interface

Edit the service file: Open /etc/systemd/system/ollama.service and add the following line inside the [Service] section:

#add after the Environment line this line to allow all hosts from 0.0.0.0 to 255.255.255.255
Environment="OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0"
Environment="OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=480"
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl restart ollama



single line command to do it:
sudo sed -i '/Environment="PATH=/a Environment="OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0"\nEnvironment="OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=4800"' /etc/systemd/system/ollama.service && sudo systemctl daemon-reload && sudo systemctl restart ollama
